          "text": "/goal Implement issue #60 in this repo: add a /auth/v1 auth surface to apps/api (register, login, me, and sessions-as-resource: list / current / revoke-one / revoke-others) backed by revocable server-side sessions using an opaque token (crypto.randomBytes(32), base64url) hashed at rest with SHA-256 (raw token never stored), plus a NestJS guard that reads the token (Authorization Bearer, then HttpOnly cookie), looks it up, and puts the verified userId into a request-scoped AuthContext (@CurrentUser) for /api/v1 routes, feeding TenantDbService.runAs(userId) so RLS runs under a trusted tenant; userId must never come from client input. Use code-first OpenAPI: class-validator DTOs behind a global ValidationPipe (whitelist + forbidNonWhitelisted) and @nestjs/swagger emitting openapi.json; explicit response types, never ad-hoc objects. Full architecture is in SPEC.md section 22.0; the endpoint list, hard requirements, and acceptance criteria are in the appended stdin block. Re-introduce the chat endpoints under /api/v1, guard-protected and owner-scoped by the verified id. When done, run the api unit tests and apps/api/scripts/rls-test.sh, fix failures, then commit your work on the current git branch feat/60-auth-v1 using conventional commits. Do not push and do not open a PR.\n\n<stdin>\n# Issue #60 — feat(api): auth in apps/api — /auth/v1, revocable server-side sessions\n\nGitHub: https://github.com/leon0399/llame/issues/60\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n`apps/api` owns authentication. Implement the **`/auth/v1`** surface with **revocable server-side sessions** (opaque token, hashed at rest) and a guard that establishes a trusted tenant identity for **`/api/v1`** → `TenantDbService.runAs(userId)`. Per SPEC **§22.0**. Closes the #61 IDOR; **prerequisite for #55**.\n\n## Endpoints (`/auth/v1`)\n```\nPOST   /auth/v1/login                 login (verb)        POST /auth/v1/register\nGET    /auth/v1/me                    current user\nGET    /auth/v1/sessions              list my sessions (with device metadata)\nGET|DELETE /auth/v1/sessions/current  current session / logout\nDELETE /auth/v1/sessions/{id}         revoke a specific session\nDELETE /auth/v1/sessions              revoke all OTHERS (default); ?scope=all incl. current\n```\n\n## Requirements\n- **Schema migration** on `sessions`: `token_hash text NOT NULL` (SHA-256 hex; the lookup key; raw token never stored), `created_at`, `last_seen_at`, + **device metadata** (`user_agent`, `ip`) for the listing UI; retire the raw `session_token` PK.\n- **Token:** `crypto.randomBytes(32)` (CSPRNG) base64url; at-rest **SHA-256** only. Not `uuid()`/`Math.random()`.\n- **Guard:** read token (`Authorization: Bearer` then `HttpOnly` cookie), `hash → sessions` lookup, check not-expired/revoked/idle → `userId` into a request-scoped `AuthContext` (`@CurrentUser`). `/api/v1/*` requires it; any failure → **401, fail closed**. `userId` is **never** read from body/query/params.\n- **Cookie** (web): `HttpOnly; Secure; SameSite`. Raw token never logged. **Bearer** for mobile — same lookup.\n- **Rotation** on privilege/credential change (session-fixation). **Revocation** by row delete (logout / sign-out-everywhere / breach).\n- Identity feeds `runAs` → RLS; validate `userId` non-empty before `runAs`.\n- **Typed contract (code-first OpenAPI).** Every endpoint takes a class-validator **DTO** behind a global `ValidationPipe` (`whitelist + forbidNonWhitelisted` → fail-closed input validation, which the auth surface needs regardless). `@nestjs/swagger` derives **`openapi.json`** from those DTOs + explicit response types (e.g. `PublicUser`, never ad-hoc objects), emitted as a build artifact. No hand-written spec; **client/SDK codegen is deferred** (post-v0.1, once the surface is stable / a non-TS consumer exists) — the spec is the durable asset, the generated client is disposable.\n\n## Acceptance\n- [ ] `/auth/v1` login + sessions-as-resource implemented; sessions hashed-at-rest, opaque.\n- [ ] Guard validates per request; missing/unknown/expired/**revoked** → 401.\n- [ ] **Revocation test:** revoke → next request 401. **Cross-tenant test:** A can't touch B's data; cross-tenant read = 0 rows.\n- [ ] Re-introduced chat endpoints live under `/api/v1`, guard-protected + owner-scoped by the verified id.\n- [ ] Input validated via DTO + `ValidationPipe` (unknown/invalid field → **400**); `openapi.json` is emitted on build and covers `/auth/v1` + the `/api/v1` chat routes (SSE stream endpoint excepted — documented, not codegen-modeled).\n\n## Out of scope\nOAuth/passkey providers (later); full RBAC / org membership → v0.3; the apps/web thin-client refactor → #63; the streaming loop → #55. **Client/mobile SDK codegen** off the spec → deferred until a stable surface + real second consumer.\n\nConsumes #53. **Blocks #55 and #63.**\n\n</stdin>",
